ent, not normative.\n\n### ADR Question\n\nThis changes the project-workspace interface (where the workspace looks for project knowledge). That's an architectural decision. Should we add an ADR, or is the issue + PR sufficient since it's extending an existing convention rather than introducing a new one?\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Update `setup.sh` to look for `.agents/workspace-context/` (new) with fallback to `config/agent_context/` (old) for backward compatibility during transition\n- Update all documentation references in the same PR\n- Update `project_agents_guide.md` template to show expanded `.agents/` structure\n- Consider whether `generate_knowledge.sh` removal (#274) should happen in this PR or separately\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772132467,"nonce":"aPr39I4TsHweLNmPjPv/xc8cCyM=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uMuchzwAAAAVhs_zk"},"status":2}]}